    The code above is executed on the selection of an exercise. This code
    calls the <em>getResourceURL</em> method, which generates the URL.
    Following is a code of the <em>getResourceURL</em> method.<br><br>
    <pre>
      var getResourceURL = function (obj) {
        if (!$.isEmptyObject(obj)) {
          var odsa_url = odsa_launch_url + '?' + $.param(obj);
          var urlParams = {
            'embed_type': 'basic_lti',
            'url': odsa_url
          };
          return return_url + '?' + $.param(urlParams);
        }
        return '';
      };
    </pre>
    Here return_url is the url of the tool consumer to which result has to be
    returned and urlParams contains launch url of exercise that tool consumer
    will add in the Submission Tool URL. <br><br>

    Once Submission Tool URL is added, instructors can publish the exercise to
    make that exercise available for students. <br><br>

    This is how OpenDSA makes use of LTI, which allows the OpenDSA exercises to
    be seamlessly added into the courses in Learning Management Systems.

